{"created_at":"1782738258","event_type":"set","payload":{"field":"implementation_plan:set","value":"[\"Add or enrich packet-work so agents can fetch deterministic state for a work item without guessing.\", \"Add observability metrics for Slate operations, lifecycle transitions, proof gates, and packet requests using patina:measure.\", \"Expose missing top-level Patina CLI parity for read-only Slate operations first: list, ready, blocked, history, prompt, handoff, packet.\", \"Keep the outside-in Rust slate-observer in Grafana-Labs as the proving harness for state shape, metrics, and Grafana dashboards.\", \"Document the agent protocol: answer \\u201cwhat is going on?\\u201d only after reading Slate packet/history/measure evidence.\"]"},"work_id":"slate-observability-packet"}
{"created_at":"1782738259","event_type":"set","payload":{"field":"proof_plan:set","value":"[\"[ ] cargo test passes in patina-child-slate after packet/metrics changes.\", \"[ ] `patina child call slate-manager patina:slate/control@0.1.0.packet-work` returns status, proof progress, blockers, evidence, and next action for this work item.\", \"[ ] Slate emits operation/check/packet metrics through the existing patina:measure import or an equivalent host-visible path.\", \"[ ] Grafana-Labs Rust slate-observer can consume the updated packet shape without losing current /state and /metrics behavior.\", \"[ ] Documentation explains the agent evidence protocol and the boundaries between Slate child, Patina host CLI, and Grafana observer.\"]"},"work_id":"slate-observability-packet"}
